title: Retired
description: After 39 1/2 years as an RF Systems engineer working at several companies in my career, I have decided it was time to retire. Rather than continuing the rat race in a fast paced, insane work environment, working with unreasonable people, I will be working towards restoration of antiques at my slow attentive to detail pace. In the morning, rather than rushing to work, fighting constipated traffic where drivers assume they own the road, I will be having coffee, reading the paper and taking long slow strolls surrounded by tress and wildlife. Rather than dealing with egos, micro-managers, cliques and having a plan, my plan is to deal with old wood, fillers and finishes. Rather than worrying about raises (or lack of), biased reviews and unreasonable people, I will worry about the grit of sandpaper, the type of finish for a piece of wood and dealing with the kind people at the paint store. There are many whom I have worked with over the years I will dearly miss. They have always given me hope, inspiration, and the reason to continue the project or task in spite of the unwarranted expectations of those less qualified to know the tasks complexity. However, it never fails; there always seems be that few who can impede the best of intentions, place unnecessary stress on those that care, create unrealistic milestone and punish those doing their best in their own way. Thankfully, I will no longer be part of that environment. I can only hope those that are still part of that stressful environment are finally recognized for their abilities rather than having to kowtow to megalomaniacs performing tasks that has no relevance in reality other than in the delusional mind of the bad manager.
